==German==
===Etymology===
From Venecian ''caviaro'', which is loaned from Turkish ''[[havyar]]''. This in turn from the Iranian word for the [[sturgeon]], literally "egg-bearing fish".
===Noun===
'''Kaviar''' ''m''
# [[caviar]]
#:''Der '''Kaviar''' schmeckt aber wieder mal vorzüglich! Woher beziehen Sie ihn?''
# (paraphilic slang, vulgar) [[feces]]
#:''Gib mir deinen '''Kaviar'''!''
